he BEAT S without drugs, not losing a single

By have clue -- will travel on Thursday, July 13, 2000 - 01:06 pm:

Yep, Jells are very balanced in terms of their attacks. A lot depends on your fighting style and how high you build your attack stats -- and with some of the raising styles floating around, just about any monster can get its attack stats up to the heights...

POW-Jells get some nice low-cost moves. Jell Top (D/S/E/E for 17) is VERY nice -- compare that to a Pixie's Lightning (D/A/E/E for 25), and I know I used THAT out the wazoo when winning with my Pixies. Spiked Top (C/A/E/D for 28), Two Whips (C/A/D/- for 22), Pierce (C/C/-/E for 21), Whip (D/A/E/- for 14) and particularly Suffocation (B/C/E/B for 24) are all very efficient, plus you get Bloodsuction as a low-% lifedrainer. Jell Cube is useless, but you can't have everything...

What you have there is a perfect chip-away monster; focus on POW and SKI and it'll be able to hit almost anyone reliably and do substantial damage with every shot, from three different ranges. A Muddy Jell or Wall Mimic could ROCK if raised correctly.

INT-Jells, on the other hand, are stuck at range (then again, so is a Phoenix, and nobody complains about THEM). You're short on moves for quite some time (the low-hit% Cannon and Slingshot, plus Beam Gun) until you unlock Beam Cannon, which can make some intermediate battles interesting. Even at high levels, you're going to be relying on very high-Guts moves (Jell Copter, Beam Cannon, Gatling Gun) which are GREAT -- unless they miss. ;)

jeff. who prefers slow-but-sure to massive-and-flashy, personally...

By have clue -- will travel on Thursday, July 13, 2000 - 10:11 pm:

I didn't miss it, I just don't like it that much. ;)

Jell Press is C/A/E/E for 30.
Two Whips is C/A/D/- for 22.

The mild Sharpness advantage is there for Jell Press, but with the mediocre Jell Guts regeneration, I'd go with the Two Whips from the same range for the same damage and hit %. Or Suffocation (B/C/E/B for 24), with sufficient Skill to make it hit.

Furthermore, look at Spiked Top: C/A/E/D for 28. It's actually a BETTER attack than Jell Press for slightly less Guts!
